\n  }\r\n  @media screen and (max-width: 480px) {\r\n    .logo {\r\n        font-size: 150px;\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n  </style>\r\n</head>\r\n<body>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"container-fluid\">\r\n			<div class=\"row\">\r\n				<div class=\"col-lg-12\">\r\n					<div class=\"carousel slide\" data-ride=\"carousel\" id=\"my-slide\">\r\n					<!--wrapper for slides-->\r\n					<div class=\"carousel-inner\" role=\"listbox\">\r\n						<div class=\"item active\">\r\n							<img class=\"img-responsive \" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screenshot-151.png\"  />\r\n						</div>\r\n\r\n						<div class=\"item\">\r\n							<img class=\"img-responsive \" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Screenshot-149-1.png\"  /> \r\n							\r\n						</div>\r\n					</div>\r\n\r\n					<!-- control or next and prev buttons-->\r\n						<a class=\"left carousel-control\" href=\"#my-slide\" role=\"button\" data-slide=\"prev\">\r\n							<span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\r\n						</a>\r\n						<a class=\"right carousel-control\" href=\"#my-slide\" role=\"button\" data-slide=\"next\">\r\n							<span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\r\n						</a>\r\n\r\n					<!--Indicators dot nov-->\r\n						<ol class=\"carousel-indicators\">\r\n							<li data-target=\"#my-slide\" data-slide-to=\"0\" class=\"active\"></li>\r\n							<li data-target=\"#my-slide\" data-slide-to=\"1\" ></li>\r\n						</ol>\r\n\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>	\r\n\r\n		</div><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"jumbotron text-center\">\r\n  <h1>FREEPATHSHALA</h1> \r\n  <p>a Gurgaon based NGO, takes a step\r\nfurther to bring up the cause of EDUCATION FOR THE\r\nCHILDREN OF MIGRANT WORKERS - a class of our society\r\nwhich is always on move.\r\n</p> \r\n  \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<!-- Container (About Section) -->\r\n<div id=\"about\" class=\"container-fluid\">\r\n  <div class=\"row\">\r\n    <div class=\"col-sm-8\">\r\n      <h2>About freepathshala</h2><br>\r\n      <h4><strong>Education is the most powerful weapon which you can use to change the world.</h4>\r\n      <p style=\"text-align:right;\">-Nelson Rolihlahla Mandela</p></strong>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Freepathshala is a Gurgaon based NGO which ensures to take care of the educational requirements of children of the most neglected class of our society  Migrant Workers. With the realization of CHANGE being the only constant in their lives, we help them to bring steadiness in their day to day undulations by providing their kids with education along with health concerns. Also, we encourage our little minds to actively participate in extracurricular activities with the view of their overall development.<br></P>\r\n      \r\n      <br>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-sm-4\">\r\n      <span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-signal logo\"></span>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"container-fluid bg-grey\">\r\n  <div class=\"row\">\r\n    <div class=\"col-sm-4\">\r\n      <span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-globe logo slideanim\"></span>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-sm-8\">\r\n      \r\n      <h4><strong>MISSION AND VISION:<br><br><br>\r\n      Our mission At FREEPATHSHALA, we envision an India where every child of a nations builder is blessed with the invaluable education.</h4>\r\nOur mission is to envisage a FREEPATHSHALA in the vicinity of every kilometer of the nation.\r\n\r\nWe anticipate ourselves chasing our dreams at the velocity of<br><br>\r\nONE FREEPATHSHALA PER KILOMETER.</strong> </p>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"container-fluid bg-grey\">\r\n  <div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-sm-4\">\r\n      <span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-flag logo slideanim\"></span>\r\n    </div>\r\n   \r\n    <div class=\"col-sm-8\">\r\n      \r\n      <h4><strong>EVENTS AND INITIATIVES<br><br><br>\r\n      </strong> </p>\r\n       Freepathshala has done some successful events and take some of the great initiatives in the field of the education of the children\'s of the migrant workers.\r\n\r\nSome of the Events and Initiatives are:- \r\n<a href=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/events/\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Know More</button></a>\r\n\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n \r\n\r\n','','','publish','closed','closed','','home','','','2017-07-04 09:31:38','2017-07-04 09:31:38','',0,'https://vikas111blog.wordpress.com/?page_id=6',1,'page','',0),(151,1,'2017-05-24 13:28:31','2017-05-24 13:28:31',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','151','','','2017-05-27 21:34:40','2017-05-27 21:34:40','',0,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/05/24/',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(154,1,'2017-05-08 07:24:30','2017-05-08 07:24:30','Freepathshala provide various programs which will improve the children\'s physical as well as mental skills.Over all personality development is important for the children\'s to cope with the mainstream race of the real world.\r\nThese type of activities are necessary to up-skilled the talents of the children\'s.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/18403247_1413004985426901_2367617088384845402_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/14900600_1210859692308099_4760640504443495436_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>1) Design Thinking Workshop:</strong> In association with the team of INDES, a non-profit organisation based in the Delhi/NCR region, we conducted a workshop on Investigating designs for the kids. Investigating designs is usually a detailed research performed which includes collecting data, the path to be followed and then analyzing the gathered information using designs and architectures. The students were required to build a roadmap that they follow to reach the pathshala each morning from their respective houses. The goal of the activity was to drive the already available knowledge to the kids to make substantial conclusions whenever required, to push their minds to ponder over other ways to solve a problem. The roadmap would help the kids think of other possible ways of reaching the pathshala if any one of the route is blocked due to some reason. It may also help them guide people to either the pathshala or their houses. If a situation arises that the kid is lost in the city, the design would help him identify the possible routes to reach his destination. The activity was performed in the month of march in HUDA park. The students counted trees in the region by drawing circles and also drafted a pathway from the park with the elements that they usually spot on the way. The task is our step to provide the kids with an out of the box thinking capability and for the comprehensive development of the kids.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-660\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/17361630_1649160552045760_7311229945647874152_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"308\" height=\"410\" /> <img class=\" wp-image-661 alignnone\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/17362431_1649160612045754_5807452170966717960_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"308\" height=\"410\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>2) Robotics:</strong> Makers Workshop by Mr. Harkrishan Singh and his team was organised for our kids at our Sector 51 pathshala. This workshop goal was to espouse the popular maker movement. Maker culture is a movement that embraces do-it-yourself tinkering with electronics and physical objects, it focuses on learning and trying out new practical skills, building a community of resources and experimenting. Through this kids start to understand how simple machines work and it also imparts them with problem solving skills and creativity. In our workshop kids were taught to make their own ARTBOTS that could draw for them. They made the BOTS with all that was available to them and some other electronic devices. Creativity flowed as we saw extensive varieties of BOTS. Kids started having so much fun that they did not realise how much they were learning through it. Instead of something static, you can get the pieces moving and that makes the activity way more amusing. Children were also taught about the basic electronic parts and how to set them up. Kids who learn how to plan and build structures and projects when theyre young can continue to apply these concepts as theyre exposed to more complex ideas. Credits to Mr. Ashish Sharma for the pictures and videos and to Ms. Meghna Bhutoria for connecting. At the end of the session all of the kids posed with their BOTS with pride.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-658\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/unnamed.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"884\" height=\"662\" />\r\n<pre class=\"aLF-aPX-K0-aPE aLF-aPX-aLK-ayr-auR\"></pre>','Up-Skilling','This is the excerpt for a featured post.','publish','open','open','','featured-content','','','2017-06-28 15:06:35','2017-06-28 15:06:35','',0,'https://vikas111blog.wordpress.com/?p=8',0,'post','',0),(156,1,'2017-05-24 13:28:31','2017-05-24 13:28:31',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','156','','','2017-06-07 12:42:49','2017-06-07 12:42:49','',0,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/05/24/',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(233,1,'2017-05-25 13:13:17','2017-05-25 13:13:17','<h4>Roshan Kumar Rawat</h4>\r\nMBA HR, MSW\r\n15yr Corporate Exposure as HR Professional.\r\nBuilding opportunities to educate construction workers kids.\r\n<h4>Shalini Bandooni</h4>\r\nB.Sc Gold Medallist, B.ed 2005, Ex Teacher Govt College\r\nShe advise us on Academics\r\n<h4>Tanishk Bhardwaj</h4>\r\nSecurities Compliance | 100 Young Social Entrepreneurs of Color | Asian High Potential Young Leaders Invitee.\r\nHe advise us on Funding, Social Media and People Operations.\r\n<h4>Dr. Shesadev Nayak</h4>\r\nProfessor-Schoo