ovide various programs which will improve the children\'s physical as well as mental skills.Over all personality development is important for the children\'s to cope with the mainstream race of the real world.\r\nThese type of activities are necessary to up-skilled the talents of the children\'s.\r\n\r\n1) <b>Design Thinking:-</b> Under the proper guidance and experts advice with professional teachers children\'s hidden gems and talent will be revealed and give them a proper way by shaping there minds to use there talents in there life.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/18403247_1413004985426901_2367617088384845402_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/14900600_1210859692308099_4760640504443495436_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>2)Robotics Design:</strong> In association with the team of INDES, a non-profit organisation based in the Delhi/NCR region, we conducted a workshop on Investigating designs for the kids. Investigating designs is usually a detailed research performed which includes collecting data, the path to be followed and then analyzing the gathered information using designs and architectures. The students were required to build a roadmap that they follow to reach the pathshala each morning from their respective houses. The goal of the activity was to drive the already available knowledge to the kids to make substantial conclusions whenever required, to push their minds to ponder over other ways to solve a problem. The roadmap would help the kids think of other possible ways of reaching the pathshala if any one of the route is blocked due to some reason. It may also help them guide people to either the pathshala or their houses. If a situation arises that the kid is lost in the city, the design would help him identify the possible routes to reach his destination. The 