the route is blocked due to some reason. It may also help them guide people to either the pathshala or their houses. If a situation arises that the kid is lost in the city, the design would help him identify the possible routes to reach his destination. The activity was performed in the month of march in HUDA park. The students counted trees in the region by drawing circles and also drafted a pathway from the park with the elements that they usually spot on the way. The task is our step to provide the kids with an out of the box thinking capability and for the comprehensive development of the kids.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-660\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/17361630_1649160552045760_7311229945647874152_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"308\" height=\"410\" /> <img class=\" wp-image-661 alignnone\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/17362431_1649160612045754_5807452170966717960_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"308\" height=\"410\" />\n\n<strong>3) Robotics:</strong> Makers Workshop by Mr. Harkrishan Singh and his team was organised for our kids at our Sector 51 pathshala. This workshop goal was to espouse the popular maker movement. Maker culture is a movement that embraces do-it-yourself tinkering with electronics and physical objects, it focuses on learning and trying out new practical skills, building a community of resources and experimenting. Through this kids start to understand how simple machines work and it also imparts them with problem solving skills and creativity. In our workshop kids were taught to make their own ARTBOTS that could draw for them. They made the BOTS with all that was available to them and some other electronic devices. Creativity flowed as we saw extensive varieties of BOTS. Kids started having so much fun that they did not realise how much they were learning through it. Instead of something static, you can get the pieces moving and that makes the activity way more amusing. Children were also taught about the basic electronic parts and how to set them up. Kids who learn how to plan and build structures and projects when theyre young can continue to apply these concepts as theyre exposed to more complex ideas. Credits to Mr. Ashish Sharma for the pictures and videos and to Ms. Meghna Bhutoria for connecting. At the end of the session all of the kids posed with their BOTS with pride.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-658\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/unnamed.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"884\" height=\"662\" />\n<pre class=\"aLF-aPX-K0-aPE aLF-aPX-aLK-ayr-auR\"></pre>','Up-Skilling','This is the excerpt for a featured post.','inherit','closed','closed','','154-autosave-v1','','','2017-06-28 15:06:03','2017-06-28 15:06:03','',154,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/05/154-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(269,1,'2017-05-25 14:20:44','2017-05-25 14:20:44','','Home','This is the home page\'s excerpt','inherit','closed','closed','','150-revision-v1','','','2017-05-25 14:20:44','2017-05-25 14:20:44','',150,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/05/150-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(260,1,'2017-05-25 14:13:08','2017-05-25 14:13:08','<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-252\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/child.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"991\" height=\"676\" />Welcome to your new site! You can edit this page by clicking on the Edit link. For more information about customizing your site check out <a href=\"https://www.google.co.in/?client=safari&amp;channel=mac_bm&amp;gws_rd=cr&amp;ei=TPcOWe24NcLfvgSE-ITIAg\">Home</a>','Home','This is the home page\'s excerpt','inherit','closed','closed','','150-revision-v1','','','2017-05-25 14:13:08','2017-05-25 14:13:08','',150,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/05/150-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(678,1,'2017-07-04 09:09:14','2017-07-04 09:09:14','Taking care of the Health of the children\'s is one of the prior concern of the Freepathshala. And taking mind in that we do have lots of activities and check-ups of the children\'s .\r\n\r\nFollowing are some steps in the Health section is :-\r\n\r\n1) <b> EYE CHECK-UPS:-</b> Freepathshala has done eye check up for the children after every four months with proper machinery and medicines from the eye specialized doctor.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nTo start off the month of October\'16 our team in association with <strong>The team of Eye Q vision organised a eye checkup camp</strong>. Regardless of age or physical health, it is important for everyone to have regular eye examinations. Regular tests are one of the best ways to protect vision because it can detect eye problems at their earliest stage, when theyre most treatable. Our kids are generally not able to afford such regular checkups and thus a lot of genetic diseases remain undetected which could otherwise be treated easily.\r\n\r\nThere were <strong>78 families</strong> and <strong>40 kids</strong> who were examined. Prescriptions were provided and the kids were advised to eat of lot of green vegetables to keep their eye health under check. According to the <strong>World Health Organisation</strong>, a massive <strong>80%</strong> of all blindness is preventable and having a simple eye test on a regular basis really does make all the difference. By looking into the eyes, optician may be able to see blood vessel leaks or swelling macular which are early signs of diabetes. Similarly, they may be able to detect the early stages of glaucoma or cataracts. Such facts lead to the necessity of providing our kids with periodic checkups to prevent further complications and thus are absolutely essential.\r\n<div><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-671\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG-20170629-WA0004.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"516\" height=\"516\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/14441085_1186200824773986_2319920063021912168_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\r\n\r\n2) <b> YOGA:- </b> Regular exercise and morning exercise with the yoga instructor to maintain harmony and peace in the mind plus make them physically strong.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/14639628_1223130211081047_1549998528076974194_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\r\n\r\n3)<b>Good Touch and Bad Touch:-</b> In todays times, we hear a lot about child abuse and molestation. Each one of us want our children to be safe and secure and to protect them against all odds that come their way. As kids grow up, they start meeting new people they don\'t know and fall prey to immoral minds. Most of the time, targets are very young children, below 6-7 years of age. They are too young to understand the difference between right and wrong. Its high time, we start teaching young children about Good Touch Bad Touch to help prevent more damage. In association with the team of Hope Initiative, we decided to expound our kids about this topic. The kids were taught how to know if some person can cause them harm or already mistreats them and the measures that they could take in case they though that the person can cause them harm. Since their parents leave the house early in the morning to reach the construction site, there are many times the kids are left alone at home. Which is the time when we think the kids are the most susceptible to damage. This becomes our responsibility to equip and sensitise them to face any situation or person before the harm is done. We must all try to ensure that every kid becomes physically and emotionally strong to face every situation that must come their way.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/16266221_1302941039766630_7458161962520732968_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />','Health','This is the excerpt for your very first post.','inherit','closed','closed','','5-revision-v1','','','2017-07-04 09:09:14','2017-07-04 09:09:14','',5,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/07/5-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(263,1,'2017-05-25 14:18:29','2017-05-25 14:18:29','','cropped-children1-1.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-children1-1-jpg','','','2017-05-25 14:18:29','2017-05-25 14:18:29','',0,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/cropped-children1-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(266,1,'2017-05-25 14:19:12','2017-05-25 14:19:12','http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/cropped-photo.jpg','cropped-photo.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-photo-jpg','','','2017-05-25 14:19:12','2017-05-25 14:19:12','',0,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/cropped-photo.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(267,1,'2017-05-25 14:19:57','2017-05-25 14:19:57','http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/cropped-photo-1.jpg','cropped-photo-1.jpg','','inherit','open','closed','','cropped-photo-1-jpg','','','2017-05-25 14:19:57','2017-05-25 14:19:57','',0,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/cropped-photo-1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(667,1,'2017-06-28 15:06:35','2017-06-28 15:06:35','Freepathshala provide various programs which will improve the children\'s physical as well as mental skills.Over all personality development is important for the children\'s to cope with the mainstream race of the real world.\r\nThese type of activities are necessary to up-skilled the talents of the children\'s.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/18403247_1413004985426901_2367617088384845402_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/14900600_1210859692308099_4760640504443495436_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>1) Design Thinking Workshop:</strong> In association with the team of INDES, a non-profit organisation based in the Delhi/NCR region, we conducted a workshop on Investigating designs for the kids. Investigating designs is usually a detailed research performed which includes collecting data, the path to be followed and then analyzing the gathered information using designs and architectures. The students were required to build a roadmap that they follow to reach the pathshala each morning from their respective houses. The goal of the activity was to drive the already available knowledge to the kids to make substantial conclusions whenever required, to push their minds to ponder over other ways to solve a problem. The roadmap would help the kids think of other possible ways of reaching the pathshala if any one of the route is blocked due to some reason. It may also help them guide people to either the pathshala or their houses. If a situation arises that the kid is lost in the city, the design would help him identify the possible routes to reach his destination. The activity was performed in the month of march in HUDA park. The students counted trees in the region by drawing circles and also drafted a pathway from the park with the elements that they usually spot on the way. The task is our step to provide the kids with an out of the box thinking capability and for the comprehensive development of the kids.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-660\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/17361630_1649160552045760_7311229945647874152_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"308\" height=\"410\" /> <img class=\" wp-image-661 alignnone\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/17362431_1649160612045754_5807452170966717960_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"308\" height=\"410\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>2) Robotics:</strong> Makers Workshop by Mr. Harkrishan Singh and his team was organised for our kids at our Sector 51 pathshala. This workshop goal was to espouse the popular maker movement. Maker culture is a movement that embraces do-it-yourself tinkering with electronics and physical objects, it focuses on learning and trying out new practical skills, building a community of resources and experimenting. Through this kids start to understand how simple machines work and it also imparts them with problem solving skills and creativity. In our workshop kids were taught to make their own ARTBOTS that could draw for them. They made the BOTS with all that was available to them and some other electronic devices. Creativity flowed as we saw extensive varieties of BOTS. Kids started having so much fun that they did not realise how much they were learning through it. Instead of something static, you can get the pieces moving and that makes the activity way more amusing. Children were also taught about the basic electronic parts and how to set them up. Kids who learn how to plan and build structures and projects when theyre young can continue to apply these concepts as theyre exposed to more complex ideas. Credits to Mr. Ashish Sharma for the pictures and videos and to Ms. Meghna Bhutoria for connecting. At the end of the session all of the kids posed with their BOTS with pride.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-658\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/unnamed.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"884\" height=\"662\" />\r\n<pre class=\"aLF-aPX-K0-aPE aLF-aPX-aLK-ayr-auR\"></pre>','Up-Skilling','This is the excerpt for a featured post.','inherit','closed','closed','','154-revision-v1','','','2017-06-28 15:06:35','2017-06-28 15:06:35','',154,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/06/154-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(666,1,'2017-06-27 16:37:54','2017-06-27 16:37:54','Freepathshala provide various programs which will improve the children\'s physical as well as mental skills.Over all personality development is important for the children\'s to cope with the mainstream race of the real world.\r\nThese type of activities are necessary to up-skilled the talents of the children\'s.\r\n\r\n1) <b>Design Thinking:-</b> Under the proper guid