fosys<img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"http://rs1053.pbsrc.com/albums/s479/damianfeijoo/Icons/Linkedin.gif~c200\" alt=\"Linkedin\" width=\"21\" height=\"21\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h5>Facebook Community Manager</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Kyle Lobo,</strong> Don Bosco Institute of Technology Mumbai <img class=\"alignnone \" src=\"http://rs1053.pbsrc.com/albums/s479/damianfeijoo/Icons/Linkedin.gif~c200\" alt=\"Linkedin\" width=\"29\" height=\"29\" /></li>\r\n</ul>','The Team','','inherit','closed','closed','','140-revision-v1','','','2017-05-26 07:08:04','2017-05-26 07:08:04','',140,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/05/140-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(321,1,'2017-05-26 07:28:45','2017-05-26 07:28:45','<p> hello','Home','This is the home page\'s excerpt','inherit','closed','closed','','150-revision-v1','','','2017-05-26 07:28:45','2017-05-26 07:28:45','',150,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/05/150-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(322,1,'2017-05-26 07:31:36','2017-05-26 07:31:36','','Home','This is the home page\'s excerpt','inherit','closed','closed','','150-revision-v1','','','2017-05-26 07:31:36','2017-05-26 07:31:36','',150,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/05/150-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(325,1,'2017-07-04 09:22:06','2017-07-04 09:22:06','Taking care of the Health of the children\'s is one of the prior concern of the Freepathshala. And taking mind in that we do have lots of activities and check-ups of the children\'s .\n\nFollowing are some steps in the Health section is :-\n\n1) <b> EYE CHECK-UPS:-</b> Freepathshala has done eye check up for the children after every four months with proper machinery and medicines from the eye specialized doctor.\n<div>\n\nTo start off the month of October\'16 our team in association with <strong>The team of Eye Q vision organised a eye checkup camp</strong>. Regardless of age or physical health, it is important for everyone to have regular eye examinations. Regular tests are one of the best ways to protect vision because it can detect eye problems at their earliest stage, when theyre most treatable. Our kids are generally not able to afford such regular checkups and thus a lot of genetic diseases remain undetected which could otherwise be treated easily.\n\nThere were <strong>78 families</strong> and <strong>40 kids</strong> who were examined. Prescriptions were provided and the kids were advised to eat of lot of green vegetables to keep their eye health under check. According to the <strong>World Health Organisation</strong>, a massive <strong>80%</strong> of all blindness is preventable and having a simple eye test on a regular basis really does make all the difference. By looking into the eyes, optician may be able to see blood vessel leaks or swelling macular which are early signs of diabetes. Similarly, they may be able to detect the early stages of glaucoma or cataracts. Such facts lead to the necessity of providing our kids with periodic checkups to prevent further complications and thus are absolutely essential.\n<div><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-671\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/IMG-20170629-WA0004.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"516\" height=\"516\" /></div>\n</div>\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/14441085_1186200824773986_2319920063021912168_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\n\n2) <b> YOGA:- </b> Regular exercise and morning exercise with the yoga instructor to maintain harmony and peace in the mind plus make them physically strong.\n\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/14639628_1223130211081047_1549998528076974194_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\n\n3)<b>Good Touch and Bad Touch:-</b> In todays times, we hear a lot about child abuse and molestation. Each one of us want our children to be safe and secure and to protect them against all odds that come their way. As kids grow up, they start meeting new people they don\'t know and fall prey to immoral minds. Most of the time, targets are very young children, below 6-7 years of age. They are too young to understand the difference between right and wrong. Its high time, we start teaching young children about Good Touch Bad Touch to help prevent more damage. In association with the team of Hope Initiative, we decided to expound our kids about this topic. The kids were taught how to know if some person can cause them harm or already mistreats them and the measures that they could take in case they though that the person can cause them harm. Since their parents leave the house early in the morning to reach the construction site, there are many times the kids are left alone at home. Which is the time when we think the kids are the most susceptible to damage. This becomes our responsibility to equip and sensitise them to face any situation or person before the harm is done. We must all try to ensure that every kid becomes physically and emotionally strong to face every situation that must come their way.\n\n<img class=\"wrap align-right\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/16266221_1302941039766630_7458161962520732968_n.jpg\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1001\" />\n\n3)<strong>Meal Distribution Drive</strong><b>:- </b>With the group of Aaokhilayen Gurgaon team, we organise nutritious meals for the kids every Saturday. The meal include fruits ,like bananas ,and milk. A sumptuous repast is quiet essential in the early stages of childhood to check on the overall development of the kids. Malnutrition rates for India are extremely high, with about 38.4 per cent of children being stunted and 46 per cent underweight (National Family Health Survey, 2005-06). Calcium through milk helps in the proper development of bones in the adolescent ages. We as a country have been successfull in reducing the child mortality rates to a large extent and the challenge that arises next is to provide nutrition for their growth and their long-term well being. Fruits are quiet important to provide essential vitamins and minerals and this every weekend activity of ours becomes even more crucial since the construction workers cannot afford such wholesome meals for their kids.<b>\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-679\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/IMG-20170704-WA0002.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" />\n</b>','Health','This is the excerpt for your very first post.','inherit','closed','closed','','5-autosave-v1','','','2017-07-04 09:22:06','2017-07-04 09:22:06','',5,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/05/5-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(326,1,'2017-05-26 08:03:33','2017-05-26 08:03:33','Activities and events related to food supplements and other health care initiatives.','Health Care','This is the excerpt for your very first post.','inherit','closed','closed','','5-revision-v1','','','2017-05-26 08:03:33','2017-05-26 08:03:33','',5,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf/2017/05/5-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(334,1,'2017-06-07 12:29:58','2017-06-07 12:29:58','<center style=\"color: #008000;\">A FREEPATHSHALA PER KILOMETER!!</center>&nbsp;\n\n<center><iframe style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3508.5756214389226!2d77.06477411505907!3d28.432059499876672!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x390d1884886f654b%3A0x78fffa8dcd308f5c!2sPrinceton+Floors!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1495629681842\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></center>&nbsp;\n\n<center><b>Addres: Sirchotu Ram Park near Jain Hospital, Sec46, Gurgaon.</b></center><center><iframe style=\"border: 0;\" src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3508.695789829721!2d77.056474715059!3d28.42843480003967!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x390d1880e593af1f%3A0xbe8311f3c44a0a01!2sJain+Hospital!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1495630487013\" width=\"40