gns for the kids. Investigating designs is usually a detailed research performed which includes collecting data, the path to be followed and then analyzing the gathered information using designs and architectures. The students were required to build a roadmap that they follow to reach the pathshala each morning from their respective houses. The goal of the activity was to drive the already available knowledge to the kids to make substantial conclusions whenever required, to push their minds to ponder over other ways to solve a problem. The roadmap would help the kids think of other possible ways of reaching the pathshala if any one of the route is blocked due to some reason. It may also help them guide people to either the pathshala or their houses. If a situation arises that the kid is lost in the city, the design would help him identify the possible routes to reach his destination. The activity was performed in the month of march in HUDA park. The students counted trees in the region by drawing circles and also drafted a pathway from the park with the elements that they usually spot on the way. The task is our step to provide the kids with an out of the box thinking capability and for the comprehensive development of the kids.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-658\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/unnamed.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"884\" height=\"662\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-660\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/17361630_1649160552045760_7311229945647874152_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"304\" height=\"404\" /> <img class=\" wp-image-661 alignnone\" src=\"http://t12pathshala.co.nf/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/17362431_1649160612045754_5807452170966717960_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"308\" height=\"410\" />','Up-Skilling','This is the excerpt for a featured post.','inherit','closed','closed','','154-revision-v1','','','2017-06-27 15:10:01','2017-06-27 15:10:01','',154,'http://t12pathshala.co.nf